text.tspan: Fall 2013
As Shakespeare would write in his classic love tales, “It all
starts with a DM.”
Winter 2013
We reach the end of our high school chapter, therefore on to
college. Following several late night drives around New
Circle Road, Sam convinces Merrick to live in the same dorm
as him: Champion’s Court II.
Summer 2014
The music begins to play softly.
Sam sends an impromptu message as he is on the other side
of the world in Switzerland.
A coffee date is planned upon his return.
Spring 2018
Sam & Merrick embark on a 2-week international trip to
England & France. Train strikes mean our bold couple has to
hitchike from Nomécourt to Paris.
Thank goodness she can speak French.
Summer 2018
They visit one of their favorite cities, Chicago. Sam asks an
all-important question, and Merrick gives an all-important
answer.
The lifelong dance has begun; they have found their music within one another.
Fall 2019
A home is bought in downtown Lexington. The space is adored
by both.
Winter 2019
Time is spent traveling, remaining safe & healthy, and creating
memories with family & friends.
Merrick is teaching; Sam is developing & designing. Their team
becomes a very certain thing in a seemingly uncertain world.
Wedding day is here for Merrick and Sam.
Our book will never be closed. Life is made up of chapters; as one closes,
another opens. Our journey together has only just begun, and we’re thrilled
you’re a part of it.
2 cappucinos please.
The Cup of Commonwealth coffee date is followed by several
other romantic outings.
He asks her to go steady, and she gives an immediate yes.
The music becomes a bit clearer.
The two high schoolers think they’re cool and frequent Willy
T. at the University of Kentucky to do calculus homework.
Calc master Sam is never able to fully comprehend UK’s parking signs.
Many parking tickets are accrued.
Spring 2014
